{DIALOGUE}: Pack of Red Apples, dollar-forty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Butch is snapped out of his ass-kicking thoughts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pays English Dave and walks out of the SHOT.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LANCE'S HOUSE (KITCHEN) – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSEUP – JODY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A woman who appears to have a fondness for earrings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Both of her ears are pierced five times.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She also sports rings in her lips, eyebrows and nose.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JODY
{DIALOGUE}: ...I'll lend it to you.
{DIALOGUE}: It's a great book on body piercing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jody, Vincent and a young woman named TRUDI sit at the kitchen table of a suburban house in Echo Park.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Even though Vince is at the same table, he's not included in the conversation.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TRUDI
{DIALOGUE}: You know how they use that gun when they pierce your ears?
{DIALOGUE}: They don't use that when they pierce your nipples, do they?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JODY
{DIALOGUE}: Forget that gun.
{DIALOGUE}: That gun goes against the entire idea behind piercing.
{DIALOGUE}: All of my piercing, sixteen places on my body, every one of 'em done with a needle.
{DIALOGUE}: Five in each ear.
{DIALOGUE}: One through the nipple on my left breast.
{DIALOGUE}: One through my right nostril.
{DIALOGUE}: One through my left eyebrow.
{DIALOGUE}: One through my lip.
{DIALOGUE}: One in my clit.
{DIALOGUE}: And I wear a stud in my tongue.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vince has been letting this conversation go through one ear and out the other, until that last remark.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{META_DATA}: (interrupting)
{DIALOGUE}: Excuse me, sorry to interrupt.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm curious, why would you get a stud in your tongue?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jody looks at him and says as if it were the most obvious thing in the world.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JODY
{DIALOGUE}: It's a sex thing.
{DIALOGUE}: It helps fellatio.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: That thought never occurred to Vincent, but he can't deny it makes sense.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jody continues talking to Trudi, leaving Vincent to ponder the truth of her statement.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Vince, you can come in now!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LANCE'S BEDROOM – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lance, late 20s, is a young man with a wild and woolly appearance that goes hand-in-hand with his wild and woolly personality.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LANCE has been selling drugs his entire adult life.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's never had a day job, never filed a tax return and has never been arrested.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He wears a red flannel shirt over a "Speed Racer" tee-shirt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Three bags of heroin lie on Lance's bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lance and Vincent stand at the foot of the bed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: Now this is Panda, from Mexico.
{DIALOGUE}: Very good stuff.
{DIALOGUE}: This is Bava, different, but equally good.
{DIALOGUE}: And this is Choco from the Hartz Mountains of Germany.
{DIALOGUE}: Now the first two are the same, forty- five an ounce – those are friend prices – but this one...
{META_DATA}: (pointing to the Choco)
{DIALOGUE}: ...this one's a little more expensive.
{DIALOGUE}: It's fifty-five.
{DIALOGUE}: But when you shoot it, you'll know where that extra money went.
{DIALOGUE}: Nothing wrong with the first two.
{DIALOGUE}: It's real, real, real, good shit.
{DIALOGUE}: But this one's a fuckin' madman.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Remember, I just got back from Amsterdam.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: Am I a nigger?
{DIALOGUE}: Are you in Inglewood?
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: You're in my house.
{DIALOGUE}: White people who know the difference between good shit and bad shit, this is the house they come to.
{DIALOGUE}: My shit, I'll take the Pepsi Challenge with Amsterdam shit any ol' day of the fuckin' week.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: That's a bold statement.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: This ain't Amsterdam, Vince.
{DIALOGUE}: This is a seller's market.
{DIALOGUE}: Coke is fuckin' dead as disco.
{DIALOGUE}: Heroin's comin' back in a big fuckin' way.
{DIALOGUE}: It's this whole seventies retro.
{DIALOGUE}: Bell bottoms, heroin, they're as hot as hell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent takes out a roll of money that would choke a horse to death.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Give me three hundred worth of the madman.
{DIALOGUE}: If it's as good as you say, I'll be back for a thousand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: I just hope I still have it.
{DIALOGUE}: Whaddya think of Trudi?
{DIALOGUE}: She ain't got a boyfriend, wanna hand out an' get high?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Which one's Trudi?
{DIALOGUE}: The one with all the shit in her face?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: No, that's Jody.
{DIALOGUE}: That's my wife.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent and Lance giggle at the "faux pas."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: I'm on my way somewhere.
{DIALOGUE}: I got a dinner engagement.
{DIALOGUE}: Rain check?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: No problem?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent takes out his case of the works (utensils for shooting up).
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: You don't mind if I shoot up here?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: Me casa, su casa.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Mucho gracias.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent takes his works out of his case and, as the two continue to talk, Vince shoots up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: Still got your Malibu?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: You know what some fucker did to it the other day?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Fuckin' keyed it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: Oh man, that's fucked up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Tell me about it.
{DIALOGUE}: I had the goddamn thing in storage three years.
{DIALOGUE}: It's out five fuckin' days – five days, and some dickless piece of shit fucks with it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: They should be fuckin' killed.
{DIALOGUE}: No trial, no jury, straight to execution.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he cooks his heroin...
