{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUDDY
{DIALOGUE}: Yep.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: You don't put bourbon in it or anything?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUDDY
{DIALOGUE}: Nope.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Just checking.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Buddy exits.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent takes a look around the place.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The YUPPIES are dancing, the DINERS are biting into big, juicy hamburgers, and the icons are playing their parts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Marilyn is squealing, The Midget is paging Philip Morris, Donna Reed is making her customers drink their milk, and Dean and Jerry are acting a fool.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: Whaddya think?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: It's like a wax museum with a pulse rate.
