{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He lights it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Think nothing of it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He begins rolling one for himself.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As this time, the SOUND of a subway car fills the diner, making everything SHAKE and RATTLE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Marilyn Monroe runs to a square vent in the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An imaginary subway train BLOWS the skirt of her white dress around her ears as she lets out a squeal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The entire restaurant applauds.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Back to Mia and Vincent.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: Marsellus said you just got back from Amsterdam.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Sure did.
{DIALOGUE}: I heard you did a pilot.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: That was my fifteen minutes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: What was it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: It was show about a team of female secret agents called "Fox Force Five."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: "Fox Force Five."
{DIALOGUE}: Fox, as in we're a bunch of foxy chicks.
{DIALOGUE}: Force, as in we're a force to be reckoned with.
{DIALOGUE}: Five, as in there's one... two ... three... four... five of us.
{DIALOGUE}: There was a blonde one, Sommerset O'Neal from that show "Baton Rouge," she was the leader.
{DIALOGUE}: A Japanese one, a black one, a French one and a brunette one, me.
{DIALOGUE}: We all had special skills.
{DIALOGUE}: Sommerset had a photographic memory, the Japanese fox was a kung fu master, the black girl was a demolition expert, the French fox' specialty was sex...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: What was your specialty?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: Knives.
{DIALOGUE}: The character I played, Raven McCoy, her background was she was raised by circus performers.
{DIALOGUE}: So she grew up doing a knife act.
{DIALOGUE}: According to the show, she was the deadliest woman in the world with a knife.
{DIALOGUE}: But because she grew up in a circus, she was also something of an acrobat.
{DIALOGUE}: She could do illusions, she was a trapeze artist – when you're keeping the world safe from evil, you never know when being a trapeze artist's gonna come in handy.
{DIALOGUE}: And she knew a zillion old jokes her grandfather, an old vaudevillian, taught her.
{DIALOGUE}: If we woulda got picked up, they woulda worked in a gimmick where every episode I woulda told and ol joke.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Do you remember any of the jokes?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: Well I only got the chance to say one, 'cause we only did one show.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Tell me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: It's really corny.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: C'mon, don't be that way.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: You won't like it and I'll be embarrassed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: You told it in front of fifty million people and you can't tell it to me?
{DIALOGUE}: I promise I won't laugh.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{META_DATA}: (laughing)
{DIALOGUE}: That's what I'm afraid of.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
