{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: Oooohhhh, this doesn't sound like mindless, boring, getting-to-know- you chit-chat.
{DIALOGUE}: This sounds like you actually have something to say.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Only if you promise not to get offended.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: You can't promise something like that.
{DIALOGUE}: I have no idea what you're gonna ask.
{DIALOGUE}: You could ask me what you're gonna ask me, and my natural response could be to be offended.
{DIALOGUE}: Then, through no fault of my own, I woulda broken my promise.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Then let's just forget it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: That is an impossibility.
{DIALOGUE}: Trying to forget anything as intriguing as this would be an exercise in futility.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Is that a fact?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia nods her head: "Yes."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: Besides, it's more exciting when you don't have permission.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: What do you think about what happened to Antwan?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: Who's Antwan?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Tony Rocky Horror.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: He fell out of a window.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: That's one way to say it.
{DIALOGUE}: Another way is, he was thrown out.
{DIALOGUE}: Another was is, he was thrown out by Marsellus.
{DIALOGUE}: And even another way is, he was thrown out of a window by Marsellus because of you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: Is that a fact?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: No it's not, it's just what I heard.
