{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: No, it seemed excessive.
{DIALOGUE}: But that doesn't mean it didn't happen.
{DIALOGUE}: I heard Marsellus is very protective of you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: A husband being protective of his wife is one thing.
{DIALOGUE}: A husband almost killing another man for touching his wife's feet is something else.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: But did it happen?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: The only thing Antwan ever touched of mine was my hand, when he shook it.
{DIALOGUE}: I met Anwan once – at my wedding – then never again.
{DIALOGUE}: The truth is, nobody knows why Marsellus tossed Tony Rocky Horror out of that window except Marsellus and Tony Rocky Horror.
{DIALOGUE}: But when you scamps get together, you're worse than a sewing circle.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ED SULLIVAN AND MARILYN MONROE STAND ON STAGE
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ED SULLIVAN
{META_DATA}: (into microphone)
{DIALOGUE}: Ladies and gentlemen, now the moment you've all been waiting for, the worldfamous Jackrabbit Slim's twist contest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Patrons cheer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ed Sullivan is with Marilyn Monroe, who holds a trophy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ED SULLIVAN
{DIALOGUE}: ...One lucky couple will win this handsome trophy that Marilyn here is holding.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Marilyn holds the trophy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ED SULLIVAN
{DIALOGUE}: ...Now, who will be our first contestants?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia holds her hand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: Right here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent reacts.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: I wanna dance.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: No, no, no no, no, no, no, no.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{META_DATA}: (overlapping)
{DIALOGUE}: No, no, no, no, no, no, no.
{DIALOGUE}: I do believe Marsellus, my husband, your boss, told you to take me out and do whatever I wanted, Now, I want to dance.
{DIALOGUE}: I want to win.
{DIALOGUE}: I want that trophy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{META_DATA}: (sighs)
{DIALOGUE}: All right.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: So, dance good.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: All right, you asked for it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent and Mia walk onto the dance floor, toward Ed Sullivan.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ED SULLIVAN
{META_DATA}: (into microphone)
{DIALOGUE}: Let's hear it for our first contestants.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Patrons cheer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent and Mia walk up to the microphone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ED SULLIVAN
{DIALOGUE}: Now let's meet our first contestants here this evening.
{DIALOGUE}: Young lady, what is your name?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{META_DATA}: (into microphone)
{DIALOGUE}: Missus Mia Wallace.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ED SULLIVAN
{META_DATA}: (into microphone)
{DIALOGUE}: And, uh, how 'bout your fella here?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{META_DATA}: (into microphone)
{DIALOGUE}: Vincent Vega.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ED SULLIVAN
{META_DATA}: (into microphone)
{DIALOGUE}: All right, let's see what you can do.
{DIALOGUE}: Take it away!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia and Vincent dance to Chuck Berry's "YOU NEVER CAN TELL".
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They make hand movements as they dance.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MARSELLUS WALLACE'S HOME – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The front door FLINGS open, and Mia and Vincent dance tango- style into the house, singing a cappella the song from the previous scene.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They finish their little dance, laughing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two just stand face to face looking at each other.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Was than an uncomfortable silence?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know what that was.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: Music and drinks!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia moves away to attend to both.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent hangs up his overcoat on a big bronze coat rack in the alcove.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: I'm gonna take a piss.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: That was a little bit more information than I needed to know, but go right ahead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent shuffles off to the john.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia moves to her CD player, thumbs through a stack of CDs and selects one: k.d. lang.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The speakers BLAST OUT a high energy country number, which Mia plays air-guitar to.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She dances her way around the room and finds herself by Vincent's overcoat hanging on the rack.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She touches its sleeve.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It feels good.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her hand hoes in its pocket and pulls out his tobacco pouch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Like a little girl playing cowboy, she spreads the tobacco on some rolling paper.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Imitating what he did earlier, licks the paper and rolls it into a pretty good cigarette.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Maybe a little too fat, but not bad for a first try.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia thinks so anyway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her hand reaches back in the pocket and pulls out his Zippo lighter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She SLAPS the lighter against her leg, trying to light it fancy-style like Vince did.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: What do you know, she did it!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia's one happy clam.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She triumphantly brings the fat flame up to her fat smoke, lighting it up, then LOUDLY SNAPS the Zippo closed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Mia-made cigarette is brought up to her lips, and she takes a long, cool drag.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her hand slides the Zippo back in the overcoat pocket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But wait, her fingers touch something else.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Those fingers bring out a plastic bag with white powder inside, the madman that Vincent bought earlier from Lance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wearing a big smile, Mia brings the bag of heroin up to her face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{META_DATA}: (like you would say Bingo!)
{DIALOGUE}: Disco!
{DIALOGUE}: Vince, you little cola nut, you've been holding out on me.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BATHROOM (MARSELLUS WALLACE'S HOUSE) – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent stands at the sink, washing his hands, talking to himself in the mirror.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: One drink and leave.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't be rude, but drink your drink quickly, say goodbye, walk out the door, get in your car, and go down the road.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LIVING ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia has the unbeknownst-to-her heroin cut up into big lines on her glass top coffee table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Taking her trusty hundred dollar bill like a human Dust-Buster, she quickly snorts the fat line.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSEUP – MIA
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her head JERKS back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her hands go to her nose (which feels like it's on fucking fire), something is terribly wrong.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then... the rush hits...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BATHROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent dries his hands on a towel while he continues his dialogue with the mirror.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: ...It's a moral test of yourself, whether or not you can maintain loyalty.
{DIALOGUE}: Because when people are loyal to each other, that's very meaningful.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LIVING ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia is on all fours trying to crawl to the bathroom, but it's like she's trying to crawl with the bones removed from her knees.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Blood begins to drip from Mia's nose.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then her stomach gets into the act and she VOMITS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BATHROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vince continues.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: So you're gonna go out there, drink your drink, say "Goodnight, I've had a very lovely evening," go home, and jack off.
{DIALOGUE}: And that's all you're gonna do.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Now that he's given himself a little pep talk, Vincent's ready for whatever's waiting for him on the other side of that door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: So he goes through it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LIVING ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We follow behind Vincent as he walks from the bathroom to the living room, where he finds Mia lying on the floor like a rag doll.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's twisted on her back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Blood and puke are down her front.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And her face is contorted.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Not out of the tightness of pain, but just the opposite, the muscles in her face are so relaxed, she lies still with her mouth wide open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Slack-jawed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Jesus Christ!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent moves like greased lightning to Mia's fallen body.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bending down where she lays, he puts his fingers on her neck to check her pulse.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She slightly stirs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia is aware of Vincent over her, speaking to her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{META_DATA}: (sounding weird)
{DIALOGUE}: Mia!
{DIALOGUE}: MIA!
{DIALOGUE}: What the hell happened?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But she's unable to communicate Mia makes a few lost mumbles, but they're not distinctive enough to be called words.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent props her eyelids open and sees the story.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{META_DATA}: (to himself)
{DIALOGUE}: I'll be a son-of-a-bitch.
{META_DATA}: (to Mia)
{DIALOGUE}: Mia!
{DIALOGUE}: MIA!
{DIALOGUE}: What did you take?
{DIALOGUE}: Answer me honey, what did you take?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia is incapable of answering.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He SLAPS her face hard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent SPRINGS up and RUNS to his overcoat, hanging on the rack.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He goes through the pockets FRANTICALLY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's gone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent makes a beeline to Mia.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We follow.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{META_DATA}: (yelling to Mia)
{DIALOGUE}: Okay honey, we're getting you on your feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He reaches her and hoists the dead weight up in his arms.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: We're on our feet now, and now we're gonna talk out to the car.
{DIALOGUE}: Here we go, watch us walk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We follow behind as he hurriedly walks the practically- unconscious Mia through the house and out the front door.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VINCENT'S HOT ROD (MOVING) – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT SPEEDOMETER: red needle on a hundred.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent driving like a madman in a town without traffic laws, speeds the car into turns and up and over hills.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT.VINCENT'S HOT ROD (MOVING) – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent, one hand firmly on the wheel, the other shifting like Robocop, both eyes staring straight ahead except when he glances over at Mia.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia, slack-jawed expression, mouth gaping, posture of a bag of water.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent takes a cellular phone out of his pocket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He punches a number.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LANCE'S HOUSE – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At this late hour, LANCE has transformed from a bon vivant drug dealer to a bathrobe creature.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sits in a big comfy chair, ratty blue gym pants, a worn- out but comfortable tee-shirt that has, written on it, "TAFT, CALIFORNIA", and a moth-ridden terry cloth robe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In his hand is a bowl of Cap'n Crunch with Crunch Berries.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In front of him on the coffee table is a jug of milk, the box the Cap'n Crunch with Crunch Berries came out of, and a hash pipe in an ashtray.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the big-screen TV in front of the table is the Three Stooges, and they're getting married.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PREACHER (EMIL SIMKUS)
{META_DATA}: (on TV)
{DIALOGUE}: Hold hands, you love birds.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The phone RINGS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lance puts down his cereal and makes his way to the phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It RINGS again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jody, his wife, CALLS from the bedroom, obviously woken up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JODY (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Lance!
{DIALOGUE}: The phone's ringing!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{META_DATA}: (calling back)
{DIALOGUE}: I can hear it!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JODY (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: I thought you told those fuckin' assholes never to call this late!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{META_DATA}: (by the phone)
{DIALOGUE}: I told 'em and that's what I'm gonna tell this fuckin' asshole right now!
{META_DATA}: (he answers the phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Hello, do you know how late it is?
{DIALOGUE}: You're not supposed to be callin' me this fuckin' late.
{META_DATA}: BACK TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VINCENT IN THE MALIBU
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent is still driving like a stripe-assed ape, clutching the phone to his ear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE CUT BACK AND FORTH during the conversation.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Lance, this is Vincent, I'm in big fuckin' trouble man, I'm on my way to your place.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: Whoa, hold you horses man, what's the problem?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: You still got an adrenaline shot?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{META_DATA}: (dawning on him)
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
