{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: – get your ass in here, fuck the book!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lance angrily knocks over a pile of shit and leaves the SHOT heading for the living room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LIVING ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent is bent over Mia, talking softly to her, when Lance reenters the room.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Quit fuckin' around man and give her the shot!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lance bends down by the black case brought in by Jody.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He opens it and begins preparing the needle for injection.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: While I'm doing this, take her shirt off and find her heart.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vince rips her blouse open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jody stumbles back in the room, hanging back from the action.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Does it have to be exact?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, it has to be exact!
{DIALOGUE}: I'm giving her an injection in the heart, so I gotta exactly hit her in the heart.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Well, I don't know exactly where her heart is, I think it's here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vince points to Mia's right breast.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lance glances over and nods.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: That's it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Lance readies the injection, Vincent looks up at Jody.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: I need a big fat magic marker, got one?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JODY
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: I need a big fat magic marker, any felt pen'll do, but a magic marker would be great.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JODY
{DIALOGUE}: Hold on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jody runs to the desk, opens the top drawer and, in her enthusiasm, she pulls the drawer out of the desk, the contents of which (bills, papers, pens) spill to the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The injection is ready.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lance hands Vincent the needle.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: It's ready, I'll tell you what to do.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: You're gonna give her the shot.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: No, you're gonna give her the shot.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: I've never does this before.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: I've never done this before either, and I ain't starting now.
{DIALOGUE}: You brought 'er here, that means you give her the shot.
{DIALOGUE}: The day I bring an ODing bitch to your place, then I gotta give her the shot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jody hurriedly joins them in the huddle, a big fat red magic marker in her hand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JODY
{DIALOGUE}: Got it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent grabs the magic marker out of Jody's hand and makes a big red dot on Mia's body where her heart is.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Okay, what do I do?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: Well, you're giving her an injection of adrenaline straight to her heart.
{DIALOGUE}: But she's got a breast plate in front of her heart, so you gotta pierce through that.
{DIALOGUE}: So what you gotta do is bring the needle down in a stabbing motion.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lance demonstrates a stabbing motion, which looks like "The Shape" killing its victims in "HALLOWEEN".
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: I gotta stab her?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: If you want the needle to pierce through to her heart, you gotta stab her hard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then once you do, push down on the plunger.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: What happens after that?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: I'm curious about that myself.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: This ain't a fuckin' joke man!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: She's supposed to come out of it like –
{META_DATA}: (snaps his fingers)
{DIALOGUE}: – that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent lifts the needle up above his head in a stabbing motion.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks down on Mia.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia is fading fast.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Soon nothing will help her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent's eyes narrow, ready to do this.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Count to three.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lance, on this knees right beside Vincent, does not know what to expect.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: One...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: RED DOT on Mia's body.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Needle raised ready to strike.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: ...two...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jody's face is alive with anticipation.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NEEDLE in that air, poised like a rattler ready to strike.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: ...three!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The needle leaves frame, THRUSTING down hard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent brings the needle down hard, STABBING Mia in the chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia's head is JOLTED from the impact.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The syringe plunger is pushed down, PUMPING the adrenaline out through the needle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia's eyes POP WIDE OPEN and she lets out a HELLISH cry of the banshee.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She BOLTS UP in a sitting position, needle stuck in her chest – SCREAMING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent, Lance and Jody, who were in sitting positions in front of Mia, JUMP BACK, scared to death.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia's scream runs out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She slowly starts taking breaths of air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The other three, now scooted halfway across the room, shaken to their bones, look to see if she's alright.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LANCE
{DIALOGUE}: If you're okay, say something.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia, still breathing, not looking up at them, says in a relatively normal voice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: Something.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent and Lance collapse on their backs, exhausted and shaking from how close to death Mia came.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JODY
{DIALOGUE}: Anybody want a beer?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. VINCENT'S MALIBU (MOVING) – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent is behind the wheel driving Mia home.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No one says anything, both are still too shaken.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. FRONT OF MARSELLUS WALLACE'S HOUSE – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Malibu pulls up to the front.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia gets out without saying a word (still in a daze) and begins walking down the walkway toward her front door.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Mia!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent's out of the car, standing on the walkway, a big distance between the two.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: What are your thoughts on how to handle this?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: What's yours?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Well I'm of the opinion that Marsellus can live his whole live and never ever hear of this incident.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia smiles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: Don't worry about it.
{DIALOGUE}: If Marsellus ever heard of this, I'd be in as much trouble as you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: I seriously doubt that.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: If you can keep a secret, so can I.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Let's shake on it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two walk toward each other, holding out their hands to shake and shake they do.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Mum's the word.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia lets go of Vincent's hand and silently makes the see-no- evil, hear-no-evil, and speak-no-evil sign with her hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent smiles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: If you'll excuse me, I gotta go home and have a heart attack.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia giggles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent turns to leave.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: You still wanna hear my "FOX FORCE FIVE" joke?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent turns around.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Sure, but I think I'm still a little too petrified to laugh.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: Uh-huh.
{DIALOGUE}: You won't laugh because it's not funny.
{DIALOGUE}: But if you still wanna hear it, I'll tell it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: I can't wait.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: Three tomatoes are walking down the street, a poppa tomato, a momma tomato, and a little baby tomato.
{DIALOGUE}: The baby tomato is lagging behind the poppa and momma tomato.
{DIALOGUE}: The poppa tomato gets mad, goes over to the momma tomato and stamps on him –
{META_DATA}: (stamps on the ground)
{DIALOGUE}: – and says: catch up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They both smile, but neither laugh.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIA
{DIALOGUE}: See ya 'round, Vince.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mia turns and walks inside her house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSEUP – VINCENT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After Mia walks inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent continues to look at where she was.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He brings his hands to his lips and blows her a kiss.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then exits FRAME leaving it empty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE HEAR his Malibu START UP and DRIVE AWAY.
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FADE UP On the cartoon "SPEED RACER."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Speed is giving a detailed description of all the features on his race car "The Mac-5," which he does at the beginning of every episode.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OFF SCREEN we hear a WOMAN'S VOICE... .
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WOMAN'S VOICE (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Butch.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BUTCH'S POV
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We're in the living room of a modest two bedroom house in Alhambra, California, in the year 1972.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BUTCH'S MOTHER, 35ish, stands in the doorway leading into the living room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Next to her is a man dressed in the uniform of an American Air Force officer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The CAMERA is the perspective of a five-year old boy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MOTHER
{DIALOGUE}: Butch, stop watching TV a second.
{DIALOGUE}: We got a special visitor.
{DIALOGUE}: Now do you remember when I told you your daddy dies in a P.O.W. camp?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Uh-huh.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MOTHER
{DIALOGUE}: Well this here is Capt. Koons.
{DIALOGUE}: He was in the P.O.W. camp with Daddy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAPT. KOONS steps inside the room toward the little boy and bends down on one knee to bring him even with the boy's eyeline.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: When Koons speaks, he speaks with a slight Texas accent.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAPT. KOONS
{DIALOGUE}: Hello, little man.
{DIALOGUE}: Boy I sure heard a bunch about you.
{DIALOGUE}: See, I was a good friend of your Daddy's.
{DIALOGUE}: We were in that Hanoi pit of hell over five years together.
{DIALOGUE}: Hopefully, you'll never have to experience this yourself, but when two men are in a situation like me and your Daddy were, for as long as we were, you take on certain responsibilities of the other.
{DIALOGUE}: If it had been me who had not made it, Major Coolidge would be talkin' right now to my son Jim.
{DIALOGUE}: But the way it worked out is I'm talkin' to you, Butch.
{DIALOGUE}: I got somethin' for ya.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Captain pulls a gold wrist watch out of his pocket.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAPT. KOONS
{DIALOGUE}: This watch I got here was first purchased by your great-granddaddy.
{DIALOGUE}: It was bought during the First World War in a little general store in Knoxville, Tennessee.
{DIALOGUE}: It was bought by private Doughboy Ernie Coolidge the day he set sail for Paris.
{DIALOGUE}: It was your great-granddaddy's war watch, made by the first company to ever make wrist watches.
{DIALOGUE}: You see, up until then, people just carried pocket watches.
{DIALOGUE}: Your great-granddaddy wore that watch every day he was in the war.
{DIALOGUE}: Then when he had done his duty, he went home to your great- grandmother, took the watch off his wrist and put it in an ol' coffee can.
{DIALOGUE}: And in that can it stayed 'til your grandfather Dane Coolidge was called upon by his country to go overseas and fight the Germans once again.
{DIALOGUE}: This time they called it World War Two.
{DIALOGUE}: Your great-granddaddy gave it to your granddad for good luck.
{DIALOGUE}: Unfortunately, Dane's luck wasn't as good as his old man's.
{DIALOGUE}: Your granddad was a Marine and he was killed with all the other Marines at the battle of Wake Island.
{DIALOGUE}: Your granddad was facing death and he knew it.
{DIALOGUE}: None of those boys had any illusions about ever leavin' that island alive.
{DIALOGUE}: So three days before the Japanese took the island, your 22-year old grandfather asked a gunner on an Air Force transport named Winocki, a man he had never met before in his life, to deliver to his infant son, who he had never seen in the flesh, his gold watch.
{DIALOGUE}: Three days later, your grandfather was dead.
{DIALOGUE}: But Winocki kept his word.
{DIALOGUE}: After the war was over, he paid a visit to your grandmother, delivering to your infant father, his Dad's gold watch.
{DIALOGUE}: This watch.
{DIALOGUE}: This watch was on your Daddy's wrist when he was shot down over Hanoi.
{DIALOGUE}: He was captured and put in a Vietnamese prison camp.
{DIALOGUE}: Now he knew if the gooks ever saw the watch it'd be confiscated.
{DIALOGUE}: The way your Daddy looked at it, that watch was your birthright.
{DIALOGUE}: And he'd be damned if and slopeheads were gonna put their greasy yella hands on his boy's birthright.
{DIALOGUE}: So he hid it in the one place he knew he could hide somethin'.
{DIALOGUE}: His ass.
{DIALOGUE}: Five long years, he wore this watch up his ass.
{DIALOGUE}: Then when he died of dysentery, he gave me the watch.
{DIALOGUE}: I hid with uncomfortable hunk of metal up my ass for two years.
{DIALOGUE}: Then, after seven years, I was sent home to my family.
{DIALOGUE}: And now, little man, I give the watch to you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Capt. Koons hands the watch to Butch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A little hand comes into FRAME to accept it.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LOCKER ROOM – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The 27-year old Butch Coolidge is dressed in boxing regalia: trunks, shoes and gloves.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He lies on a table catching a few zzzzzz's before his big fight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Almost as soon as WE CUT to him, he wakes up with a start.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shaken by the bizarre memory, he wipes his sweaty face with his boxing glove.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His trainer KLONDIKE, an older fireplug, opens the door a little, sticking his head in the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pandemonium seems to be breaking out behind Klondike in the hallway.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KLONDIKE
{DIALOGUE}: It's time, Butch.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: I'm ready.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Klondike steps inside, closing the door on the WILD MOB outside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He goes to the long yellow robe hanging on a hook.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Butch hops off the table and, without a word, Klondike helps him on with the robe, which says on the back: "BATTLING BUTCH COOLIDGE".
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two men head for the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Klondike opens the door for Butch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Butch steps into the hallway, the Crowd goes apeshit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Klondike closes the door behind him, leaving us in the quiet, empty locker room.
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TITLE CARD:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "THE GOLD WATCH"
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear over the black and white title:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPORTSCASTER #1 (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: – Well Dan, that had to be the bloodiest and, hands-down, the most brutal fight this city has ever seen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The SOUND of chaos in the b.g.
{META_DATA}: FADE IN:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ALLEY (RAINING) – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A taxi is parked in a dark alley next to an auditorium.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sky is PISSIN' DOWN RAIN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE SLOWLY DOLLY toward the parked car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The SOUND of the CAR RADIO can be heard coming from inside.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPORTSCASTER #1 (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: ...Coolidge was out of there faster than I've ever seen a victorious boxer vacate the ring.
{DIALOGUE}: Do you think he knew Willis was dead?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPORTSCASTER #2 (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: My guess would be yes, Richard.
{DIALOGUE}: I could see from my position here, the frenzy in his eyes give way to the realization of what he was doing.
{DIALOGUE}: I think any man would've left the ring that fast.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. TAXI (PARKED/RAINING) – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Inside the taxi, behind the wheel, is a female cabbie named ESMARELDA VILLALOBOS.
