{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Sportscasters continue their coverage.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPORTSCASTER #1 (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Do you feel this ring death tragedy will have an effect on the world of boxing?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPORTSCASTER #2 (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh Dan, a tragedy like this can't help but shake the world of boxing to its very foundation.
{DIALOGUE}: But it's of paramount importance that during the sad weeks ahead, the eyes of the W.B.A. remain firmly fixed on the –
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLICK – Esmarelda shuts off the radio.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She takes a sip of coffee, then hears a NOISE behind her in the alley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She sticks her head out of the car door to see:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BOXING AUDITORIUM (RAINING) – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A window about three stories high opens on the auditorium- side of the alley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A gym bag is tossed out into a garbage dumpster below the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then, Butch Coolidge, still dressed in boxing trunks, shoes, gloves and yellow robe, LEAPS to the dumpster below.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ESMARELDA'S REACTION takes in the strangeness of this sight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gym bag in hand, Butch CLIMBS out of the dumpster and RUNS to the taxi.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Before he climbs in, he takes off his robe and throws it to the ground.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. TAXI (PARKED / RAINING) – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Butch, soaking wet, naked except for trunks, shoes and gloves, HOPS in the backseat, SLAMMING the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Esmarelda, staring straight ahead, talks to Butch through the rearview mirror:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ESMARELDA
{META_DATA}: (Spanish accent)
{DIALOGUE}: Are you the man I was supposed to pick up?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: If you're the cab I called, I'm the guy you're supposed to pick up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ESMARELDA
{DIALOGUE}: Where to?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: Outta here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ignition key is TWISTED.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The engine ROARS to life.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The meter is FLIPPED on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Esmarelda's bare foot STOMPS on the gas pedal.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BOXING AUDITORIUM (RAINING) – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cab WHIPS out of the alley, FISH-TAILING on the wet pavement in front of the auditorium at a rapid pace.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. WILLIS LOCKER ROOM (AUDITORIUM) – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Locker room door opens, English Dave fights his way through the pandemonium which is going on outside in the hall, shutting the door on the madness.
