{DIALOGUE}: Whatever gave you that idea?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ESMARELDA
{DIALOGUE}: No c'mon, you're him, I know you're him, tell me you're him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{META_DATA}: (drying himself with a gym towel)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ESMARELDA
{DIALOGUE}: You killed the other boxing man.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: He's dead?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ESMARELDA
{DIALOGUE}: The radio said he was dead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He finished wiping himself down.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{META_DATA}: (to himself)
{DIALOGUE}: Sorry 'bout that, Floyd.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tosses the towel out the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silence, as Butch digs in his bag for a t-shirt.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ESMARELDA
{DIALOGUE}: What does it feel like?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{META_DATA}: (finds his shirt)
{DIALOGUE}: What does what feel like?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ESMARELDA
{DIALOGUE}: Killing a man.
{DIALOGUE}: Beating another man to death with your bare hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Butch pulls on his tee-shirt.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: Are you some kinda weirdo?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ESMARELDA
{DIALOGUE}: No, it's a subject I have much interest in.
{DIALOGUE}: You are the first person I ever met who has killed somebody.
{DIALOGUE}: So, what was it like to kill a man?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: Tell ya what, you give me one of them cigarettes, I'll give you an answer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Esmarelda bounces in her seat with excitement.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ESMARELDA
{DIALOGUE}: Deal!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Butch leans forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Esmarelda, keeping her eyes on the road, passes a cigarette back to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then, still not looking behind her, she brings up her hand, a lit match in it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Butch lights his smoke, then blows out the match.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes a long drag.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: So...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at her license.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: ...Esmarelda Villalobos – is that Mexican?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ESMARELDA
{DIALOGUE}: The name is Spanish, but I'm Columbian.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: It's a very pretty name.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ESMARELDA
{DIALOGUE}: It mean "Esmarelda of the wolves."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: That's one hell of a name you got there, sister.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ESMARELDA
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you.
{DIALOGUE}: And what is your name?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: Butch.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ESMARELDA
{DIALOGUE}: Butch.
{DIALOGUE}: What does it mean?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: I'm an American, our names don't mean shit.
{DIALOGUE}: Anyway, moving right along, what is it you wanna know, Esmarelda?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ESMARELDA
{DIALOGUE}: I want to know what it feels like to kill a man –
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: – I couldn't tell ya.
{DIALOGUE}: I didn't know he was dead 'til you told me he was dead.
{DIALOGUE}: Now I know he's dead, do you wanna know how I feel about it?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Esmarelda nods her head: "yes."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: I don't feel the least little bit bad.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. PHONE BOOTH (RAINING) – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We DOLLY around a phone booth as Butch talks inside.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: What'd I tell ya, soon as the word got out a fix was in, the odds would be outta control.
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, if he was a better fighter he's be alive.
{DIALOGUE}: If he never laced up his gloves in the first place, which he never shoulda done, he'd be alive.
{DIALOGUE}: Enough about the poor unfortunate Mr. Floyd, let's talk about the rich and prosperous Mr. Butch.
{DIALOGUE}: How many bookies you spread it around with?
{META_DATA}: (PAUSE)
{DIALOGUE}: Eight?
{DIALOGUE}: How long to collect?
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: So by tomorrow evening, you'll have it all?
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: Good news Scotty, real good news – I understand a few stragglers aside.
{DIALOGUE}: Me an' Fabienne're gonna leave in the morning.
{DIALOGUE}: It should take us a couple days to get into Knoxville.
{DIALOGUE}: Next time we see each other, it'll be on Tennessee time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Butch hangs up the phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at the cab waiting to take him wherever he wants to go.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{META_DATA}: (to himself in French with English subtitles)
{DIALOGUE}: Fabienne my love, our adventure begins.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MOTEL (STOPPED / RAINING) – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Esmeralda's taxi pulled into the motel parking lot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The rain has stopped, but the night is still soaked.
