{DIALOGUE}: Sleep well, Butch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tweaks her nose, she smiles, and he turns and walks away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She drives off.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MOTEL (ROOM SIX) – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Butch enters and turns on the light.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lying curled up on the bed, fully dressed, with her back to us is Butch's French girlfriend, FABIENNE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FABIENNE
{DIALOGUE}: Keep the light off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Butch flicks the switch back, making the room dark again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: Is that better, sugar pop?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FABIENNE
{DIALOGUE}: Oui.
{DIALOGUE}: Hard day at the office?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTCH
{DIALOGUE}: Pretty hard.
{DIALOGUE}: I got into a fight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FABIENNE
{DIALOGUE}: Poor baby.
{DIALOGUE}: Can we make spoons?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Butch climbs into bed, spooning Fabienne from behind.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: When Butch and Fabienne speak to each other, they speak in babytalk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FABIENNE
