{DIALOGUE}: Feel better?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: Shit Negro, that's all you had to say.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOTEL SUITE – MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The CAMERA looks through the bedroom doorway of a hotel suite into the main area.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We SEE a crap game being played on a fancy crap table by GAMBLERS in tuxedos and LUCKY LADIES in fancy evening gowns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The CAMERA PANS to the right revealing: Sitting on a bed, phone in hand with his back to us, the tuxedo-clad WINSTON WOLF aka "THE WOLF".
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We also see The Wolf has a small notepad that he jots details in.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Is she the hysterical type?
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: When she due?
{META_DATA}: (jotting down)
{DIALOGUE}: Give me the principals' names again?
{META_DATA}: (jots down)
{DIALOGUE}: Jules...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We SEE his book.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The page has written on it:
{META_DATA}: "1265 Riverside Drive Toluca Lake 1 body (no head) Bloody shot-up car Jules (black)"
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: ...Vincent... Jimmie... Bonnie...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HE WRITES:
{META_DATA}: "Vincent (Dean Martin) Jimmie (house) Bonnie (9:30)"
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: Expect a call around 10:30.
{DIALOGUE}: It's about thirty minutes away.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll be there in ten.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hangs up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We never see his face.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TITLE CARD OVER BLACK:
{META_DATA}: "NINE MINUTES AND THIRTY-SEVEN SECONDS LATER"
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. JIMMIE'S STREET – MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A silver Porsche WHIPS the corner leading to Jimmie's home, in HYPER DRIVE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Easily doing 135 mph, the Porsche stops on a dime in front of Jimmie's house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A ringed finger touches the doorbell: DING DONG.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. JIMMIE'S HOUSE – MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jimmie opens the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see, standing in the doorway, the tuxedo-clad man.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks down to his notebook, then up at Jimmie.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: You're Jimmie, right?
{DIALOGUE}: This is your house?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JIMMIE
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{META_DATA}: (stick his hand out)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm Winston Wolf, I solve problems.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JIMMIE
{DIALOGUE}: Good, 'cause we got one.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: So I heard.
{DIALOGUE}: May I come in?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JIMMIE
{DIALOGUE}: Please do.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the dining room, Jules and Vincent stand up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: You must be Jules, which would make you Vincent.
{DIALOGUE}: Let's get down to brass tacks, gentlemen.
{DIALOGUE}: If I was informed correctly, the clock is ticking, is that right, Jimmie?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JIMMIE
{DIALOGUE}: 100%.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: Your wife, Bonnie...
{META_DATA}: (refers to his pad)
{DIALOGUE}: ...comes home at 9:30 in the AM, is that correct?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JIMMIE
{DIALOGUE}: Uh-huh.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: I was led to believe if she comes home and finds us here, she wouldn't appreciate it none too much.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JIMMIE
{DIALOGUE}: She won't at that.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: That gives us forty minutes to get the fuck outta Dodge, which, if you do what I say when I say it, should by plenty.
{DIALOGUE}: Now you got a corpse in a car, minus a head, in a garage.
{DIALOGUE}: Take me to it.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. JIMMIE'S GARAGE – MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The three men hang back as The Wolf examines the car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He studies the car in silence, opening the door, looking inside, circling it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: Jimmie?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JIMMIE
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: Do me a favor, will ya?
{DIALOGUE}: Thought I smelled some coffee in there.
{DIALOGUE}: Would you make me a cup?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JIMMIE
{DIALOGUE}: Sure, how do you take it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: Lotsa cream, lotsa sugar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jimmie exists.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Wolf continues his examination.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: About the car, is there anything I need to know?
{DIALOGUE}: Does it stall, does it make a lot of noise, does it smoke, is there gas in it, anything?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: Aside from how it looks, the car's cool.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: Positive?
{DIALOGUE}: Don't get me out on the road and I find out the brake lights don't work.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: Hey man, as far as I know, the motherfucker's tip-top.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: Good enough, let's go back to the kitchen.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. KITCHEN – MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jimmie hands The Wolf a cup of coffee.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you, Jimmie.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes a sip, then, pacing as he thinks, lays out for the three men the plan of action.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: Okay first thing, you two.
{META_DATA}: (meaning Jules and Vincent)
{DIALOGUE}: Take the body, stick it in the trunk.
{DIALOGUE}: Now Jimmie, this looks to be a pretty domesticated house.
{DIALOGUE}: That would lead me to believe that in the garage or under the sink, you got a bunch of cleansers and cleaners and shit like that, am I correct?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JIMMIE
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah.
{DIALOGUE}: Exactly.
{DIALOGUE}: Under the sink.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: Good.
{DIALOGUE}: What I need you two fellas to do is take those cleaning products and clean the inside of the car.
{DIALOGUE}: And I'm talkin' fast, fast, fast.
{DIALOGUE}: You need to go in the backseat, scoop up all those little pieces of brain and skull.
{DIALOGUE}: Get it out of there.
{DIALOGUE}: Wipe down the upholstery – now when it comes to upholstery, it don't need to be spic and span, you don't need to eat off it.
{DIALOGUE}: Give it a good once over.
{DIALOGUE}: What you need to take care of are the really messy parts.
{DIALOGUE}: The pools of blood that have collected, you gotta soak that shit up.
{DIALOGUE}: But the windows are a different story.
{DIALOGUE}: Them you really clean.
{DIALOGUE}: Get the Windex, do a good job.
{DIALOGUE}: Now Jimmie, we need to raid your linen closet.
{DIALOGUE}: I need blankets, I need comforters, I need quilts, I need bedspreads.
{DIALOGUE}: The thicker the better, the darker the better.
{DIALOGUE}: No whites, can't use 'em.
{DIALOGUE}: We need to camouflage the interior of the car.
{DIALOGUE}: We're gonna line the front seat and the backseat and the floor boards with quilts and blankets.
{DIALOGUE}: If a cop stops us and starts stickin' his big snout in the car, the subterfuge won't last.
{DIALOGUE}: But at a glance, the car will appear to be normal.
{DIALOGUE}: Jimmie – lead the way, boys – get to work.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Wolf and Jimmie turn, heading for the bedroom, leaving Vincent and Jules standing in the kitchen.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{META_DATA}: (calling after him)
{DIALOGUE}: A "please" would be nice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Wolf stops and turns around.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: Come again?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: I said a "please" would be nice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Wolf takes a step toward him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: Set is straight, Buster.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not here to say "please.
{DIALOGUE}: "I'm here to tell you want to do.
{DIALOGUE}: And if self- preservation is an instinct you possess, you better fuckin' do it and do it quick.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm here to help.
{DIALOGUE}: If my help's not appreciated, lotsa luck gentlemen.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: It ain't that way, Mr. Wolf.
{DIALOGUE}: Your help is definitely appreciated.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: I don't mean any disrespect.
{DIALOGUE}: I just don't like people barkin' orders at me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{DIALOGUE}: If I'm curt with you, it's because time is a factor.
{DIALOGUE}: I think fast, I talk fast, and I need you guys to act fast if you want to get out of this.
{DIALOGUE}: So pretty please, with sugar on top, clean the fuckin' car.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. JIMMIE'S BEDROOM – MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jimmie's gathering all the bedspreads, quilts and linen he has.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Wolf is on the phone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WOLF
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: It's a 1974 Chevy Nova.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: White.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: Nothin', except for the mess inside.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: About twenty minutes.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: Nobody who'll be missed.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: You're a good man, Joe.
{DIALOGUE}: See ya soon.
{META_DATA}: (he looks at Jimmie)
{DIALOGUE}: How we comin', Jimmie?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jimmie comes over with a handful of linen.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JIMMIE
