{DIALOGUE}: You know I could go for some breakfast.
{DIALOGUE}: Want to have breakfast with me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: Sure.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. COFFEE SHOP – MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jules and Vincent sit at a booth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In front of Vincent is a big stack of pancakes and sausages, which he eats with gusto.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jules, on the other hand, just has a cup of coffee and a muffin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He seems far away in thought.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Waitress pours a refill for both men,
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks a bunch.
{META_DATA}: (to Jules, who's nursing his coffee)
{DIALOGUE}: Want a sausage?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: Naw, I don't eat pork.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Are you Jewish?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: I ain't Jewish man, I just don't dig on swine.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Why not?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: They're filthy animals.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't eat filthy animals.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Sausages taste good.
{DIALOGUE}: Pork chops taste good.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: A sewer rat may taste like pumpkin pie.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll never know 'cause even if it did, I wouldn't eat the filthy motherfucker.
{DIALOGUE}: Pigs sleep and root in shit.
{DIALOGUE}: That's a filthy animal.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't wanna eat nothin' that ain't got enough sense to disregard its own feces.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: How about dogs?
{DIALOGUE}: Dogs eat their own feces.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: I don't eat dog either.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, but do you consider a dog to be a filthy animal?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: I wouldn't go so far as to call a dog filthy, but they're definitely dirty.
{DIALOGUE}: But a dog's got personality.
{DIALOGUE}: And personality goes a long way.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: So by that rationale, if a pig had a better personality, he's cease to be a filthy animal?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: We'd have to be talkin' 'bout one motherfuckin' charmin' pig.
{DIALOGUE}: It'd have to be the Cary Grant of pigs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two men laugh.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Good for you.
{DIALOGUE}: Lighten up a little.
{DIALOGUE}: You been sittin' there all quiet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: I just been sittin' here thinkin'.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{META_DATA}: (mouthful of food)
{DIALOGUE}: About what?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: The miracle we witnessed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: The miracle you witnessed.
{DIALOGUE}: I witnessed a freak occurrence.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: Do you know that a miracle is?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: An act of God.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: What's an act of God?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: I guess it's when God makes the impossible possible.
{DIALOGUE}: And I'm sorry Jules, but I don't think what happened this morning qualifies.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: Don't you see, Vince, that shit don't matter.
{DIALOGUE}: You're judging this thing the wrong way.
{DIALOGUE}: It's not about what.
{DIALOGUE}: It could be God stopped the bullets, he changed Coke into Pepsi, he found my fuckin' car keys.
{DIALOGUE}: You don't judge shit like this based on merit.
{DIALOGUE}: Whether or not what we experienced was an according-to-Hoyle miracle is insignificant.
{DIALOGUE}: What is significant is I felt God's touch, God got involved.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: But why?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: That's what's fuckin' wit' me!
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know why.
{DIALOGUE}: But I can't go back to sleep.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: So you're serious, you're really gonna quit?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: The life, most definitely.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent takes a bite of food.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jules takes a sip of coffee In the b.g., we see a PATRON call the Waitress.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PATRON
{DIALOGUE}: Garcon!
{DIALOGUE}: Coffee!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We recognize the patron to be Pumpkin from the first scene of Pumpkin and Honey Bunny.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: So if you're quitting the life, what'll you do?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: That's what I've been sitting here contemplating.
{DIALOGUE}: First, I'm gonna deliver this case to Marsellus.
{DIALOGUE}: Then, basically, I'm gonna walk the earth.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: What do you mean, walk the earth?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: You know, like Caine in "KUNG FU."
{DIALOGUE}: Just walk from town to town, meet people, get in adventures.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: How long do you intend to walk the earth?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: Until God puts me where he want me to be.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: What if he never does?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: If it takes forever, I'll wait forever.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: So you decided to be a bum?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: I'll just be Jules, Vincent – no more, no less.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: No Jules, you're gonna be like those pieces of shit out there who beg for change.
{DIALOGUE}: They walk around like a bunch of fuckin' zombies, they sleep in garbage bins, they eat what I throw away, and dogs piss on 'em.
{DIALOGUE}: They got a word for 'em, they're called bums.
{DIALOGUE}: And without a job, residence, or legal tender, that's what you're gonna be – a fuckin' bum!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: Look my friend, this is just where me and you differ –
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: – what happened was peculiar – no doubt about it – but it wasn't water into wine.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: All shapes and sizes, Vince.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: Stop fuckin' talkin' like that!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: If you find my answers frightening, Vincent, you should cease askin' scary questions.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: I gotta take a shit.
{DIALOGUE}: To be continued.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent exits for the restroom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jules, alone, takes a mouthful of muffin, then... Pumpkin and Honey Bunny rise with guns raised.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PUMPKIN
