{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: Your life.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm givin' you that money so I don't hafta kill your ass.
{DIALOGUE}: You read the Bible?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PUMPKIN
{DIALOGUE}: Not regularly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: There's a passage I got memorized.
{DIALOGUE}: Ezekiel 25:17.
{DIALOGUE}: "The path of the righteous man is beset on all sides by the inequities of the selfish and the tyranny of evil men.
{DIALOGUE}: Blessed is he who, in the name of charity and good will, shepherds the weak through the valley of the darkness.
{DIALOGUE}: For he is truly his brother's keeper and the finder of lost children.
{DIALOGUE}: And I will strike down upon thee with great vengeance and furious anger those who attempt to poison and destroy my brothers.
{DIALOGUE}: And you will know I am the Lord when I lay my vengeance upon you."
{DIALOGUE}: I been sayin' that shit for years.
{DIALOGUE}: And if you ever heard it, it meant your ass.
{DIALOGUE}: I never really questioned what it meant.
{DIALOGUE}: I thought it was just a coldblooded thing to say to a motherfucker 'fore you popped a cap in his ass.
{DIALOGUE}: But I saw some shit this mornin' made me think twice.
{DIALOGUE}: Now I'm thinkin', it could mean you're the evil man.
{DIALOGUE}: And I'm the righteous man.
{DIALOGUE}: And Mr. .45 here, he's the shepherd protecting my righteous ass in the valley of darkness.
{DIALOGUE}: Or is could by you're the righteous man and I'm the shepherd and it's the world that's evil and selfish.
{DIALOGUE}: I'd like that.
{DIALOGUE}: But that shit ain't the truth.
{DIALOGUE}: The truth is you're the weak.
{DIALOGUE}: And I'm the tyranny of evil men.
{DIALOGUE}: But I'm tryin'.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm tryin' real hard to be a shepherd.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jules lowers his gun, lying it on the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pumpkin looks at him, to the money in his hand, then to Yolanda.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Grabbing the trash bag full of wallets, the two RUN out the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jules, who was never risen from his seat the whole time, takes a sip of coffee.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{META_DATA}: (to himself)
{DIALOGUE}: It's cold.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pushes it aside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent appears next to Jules.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{DIALOGUE}: I think we oughta leave now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JULES
{DIALOGUE}: That's probably a good idea.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vincent throws some money on the table and Jules grabs the briefcase.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then, to the amazement of the Patrons, the Waitresses, the Cooks, the Bus Boys, and the Manager, these two bad-ass dudes – wearing UC Santa Cruz and "I'm with Stupid" tee-shirts, swim trunks, thongs and packing .45 Automatics – walk out of the coffee shop together without saying a word.
{META_DATA}: FADE OUT
{META_DATA}: THE END
